Look with me in your Bible.

54:11.310 --> 54:13.012
Every lofty opinion.

54:13.072 --> 54:16.818
Do you know anyone that loves their own opinion?

54:18.306 --> 54:21.396
Dr. Bob, before he passed, he used to sit right there where Matt is.

54:21.777 --> 54:25.229
He told me, he said, Brandon, there's only one thing in life that everybody hates.

54:25.409 --> 54:26.393
What is it, Dr. Bob?

54:27.275 --> 54:28.660
Unsolicited opinions.

54:30.346 --> 54:31.730
Unsolicited opinions.

54:32.258 --> 54:39.045
Everybody has one and everyone loves to share theirs and they are lofty and they're exalted and you need to listen to me.

54:39.566 --> 54:54.462
Every lofty opinion that is raised against the knowledge of God, it could read in the King James, every high theme, every tower, every rampart of high intellectual assertions against divine truth.

54:56.804 --> 54:58.706
Every person that comes

54:59.202 --> 55:16.461
presenting themselves as an expert with credentials, with titles, with charisma, with lofty opinions that sound good, that woo people, but when you begin to peel back the layers of the onion, they are in defiance against the knowledge of God.

55:20.064 --> 55:28.914
It means that the point is not that we are trying to win an argument for argument's sake.

55:30.306 --> 55:37.375
The point is that we want to destroy every high tower of unbelief and rebellion in the high places.

55:38.737 --> 55:43.503
And the battle of our lives is the battle of unbelief.

55:44.945 --> 55:51.072
Did you know that most of your problems in mind come back in one way to unbelief?

55:52.434 --> 55:58.802
We don't believe the promises of God in our life and it's a war.

55:59.650 --> 56:00.912
of who we're going to believe.

56:03.155 --> 56:16.054
And it's been a war over the last few years that's raging because we are realizing more and more that we live in a world of lies everywhere you look, everywhere you turn.

56:17.456 --> 56:21.282
Lies, lies, and more lies.

56:22.644 --> 56:27.491
And the most powerful thing in the entire universe is the truth.

56:28.472 --> 56:29.554
And the place

56:30.370 --> 56:37.417
The only place where you find the truth, the knowledge of God and His holy word.

56:39.118 --> 56:49.708
So listen, I am not trying to mobilize us as a church to begin to go after one another or even go after our neighbors on every infraction of error.

56:51.851 --> 56:53.772
I hope that we are mature beyond that.

56:55.154 --> 56:59.698
But where the truth is at stake in important ways,

57:00.514 --> 57:07.145
The weapons of our warfare are living and seeking to proclaim and live according to it.

57:07.926 --> 57:08.828
Look with me finally.

57:08.908 --> 57:20.668
Take every thought captive, bring into captivity, not just worldly ideologies, but every thought that enters into your mind.

57:20.728 --> 57:22.210
Listen to the terminology.

57:22.691 --> 57:24.434
It means take prisoners of war.

57:25.122 --> 57:32.800
everything that you should not be thinking, that is not honoring to God on every front, that is not edifying for the Christian life.

57:33.181 --> 57:43.506
Every thought that you have come into your mind, what the Bible is saying is you take it captive, you imprison it, you round it up.

57:44.706 --> 57:56.322
Every thought, you take a captive immediately, the Bible says, to obey Christ or to the obedience of Christ, you bring that thought under the lordship of Jesus Christ.

57:57.043 --> 58:04.413
You refuse to entertain it, you repent of it, and then you replace it with the counterpart of it that would honor God.

58:04.433 --> 58:14.386
This is why Philippians chapter four, verse eight, calls us to set our minds on that which is true and good and beautiful.

58:14.786 --> 58:20.975
every single day, because you are what you worship, and you will become what you think.

58:22.297 --> 58:23.378
You will become what you think.

58:24.840 --> 58:29.667
And over and over, Paul says that he was not found in eloquence of speech.

58:29.707 --> 58:35.074
He was not found in deceit and air, but an open plain statement of the truth.

58:35.635 --> 58:36.897
2 Corinthians 4, 2.

58:38.659 --> 58:43.346
And finally, verse 6, being ready to punish every disobedience

58:44.482 --> 58:56.964
Paul now moves from meekness and gentleness and he shows that he is ready to take action in a very authoritative way if their hearts are not humbled before him and he will deal with false teachers.

58:58.827 --> 59:05.079
And if you're new to RBC, we have done that and we will do that in every place necessary.

59:07.283 --> 59:09.266
There have been people that I have had to tell.

59:10.018 --> 59:15.626
Last Sunday was your last Sunday, you will not be coming back here because you are a wolf and you are a threat to the flock.

59:19.091 --> 59:21.795
That's just called being a good shepherd.

59:24.098 --> 59:27.443
Verse six says, being ready to punish every disobedience.

59:27.763 --> 59:29.746
This is every defiance

59:29.986 --> 59:34.373
against faithful ministry and the teaching that Paul lays out in this letter.

59:34.673 --> 59:41.984
He says, when your obedience, likely referring to your obedience to everything that Paul has been writing to them is complete or fulfilled.

59:42.766 --> 59:44.508
So he's me, but he brings authority.

59:44.769 --> 59:49.496
Jesus in the great commission says that he has all authority in heaven and earth.

59:49.937 --> 59:55.986
And the great commission is that we make disciples and we teach them to obey everything that he commanded.

59:57.474 --> 01:00:06.143
So Paul sought to bring not only the truth of ideas and doctrines, but the obedience of faith to all the nations Romans 1 5 says.

01:00:08.486 --> 01:00:14.633
He says in 2 Corinthians 2 9 that he's writing to them to see if they would be obedient in everything.

01:00:14.693 --> 01:00:18.717
And that's the report of 2 Corinthians 7.

01:00:18.777 --> 01:00:26.866
Titus reported the obedience of them all where their faith begins to take action.

01:00:27.650 --> 01:00:31.079
and their lives begin to conform to Jesus Christ.

01:00:32.462 --> 01:00:38.197
So the weapons of our warfare and our war cry is laid out.

01:00:39.600 --> 01:00:43.410
We put on the belt of truth because Jesus is the truth.

01:00:44.130 --> 01:00:49.198
We put on the breastplate of righteousness because Jesus Christ is our righteousness.

01:00:49.518 --> 01:00:54.565
We put on the shoes of the gospel of peace because Jesus Christ is our peace.

01:00:54.886 --> 01:00:59.252
We take up the shield of faith because Jesus is the author of our faith.

01:00:59.593 --> 01:01:04.761
We put on the helmet of salvation because Jesus Christ is our salvation.

01:01:05.101 --> 01:01:11.090
We take up prayer and the sword of the spirit, the word of God because Jesus is the word of God.

01:01:12.322 --> 01:01:20.795
Just as Romans 13 says, cast off the works of darkness, put on the armor of light, and in so doing, put on the Lord Jesus Christ.

01:01:22.137 --> 01:01:22.838
Let's pray together.

01:01:27.745 --> 01:01:41.266
As one Puritan prayed, Lord, direct my feet that I be not entangled in Satan's secret snares, nor fall into his hidden traps.

01:01:42.114 --> 01:01:49.505
defend us from a sailing foes, from evil circumstances, from myself.

01:01:51.027 --> 01:01:53.812
Our adversaries are part and parcel of our nature.

01:01:54.072 --> 01:01:56.756
They cling to us as our very skin.

01:01:56.776 --> 01:01:59.981
I cannot escape their contact.

01:02:01.143 --> 01:02:03.066
Am I rising up and sitting down?

01:02:03.106 --> 01:02:06.130
They attach themselves to me.

01:02:06.190 --> 01:02:08.353
They entice me with constant baits.

01:02:09.495 --> 01:02:11.378
My enemy is within the citadel.

01:02:12.098 --> 01:02:15.846
Come with almighty power and cast him out.

01:02:15.866 --> 01:02:22.258
Pierce him to death and abolish within me every particle of carnal life this day.

01:02:22.278 --> 01:02:24.824
In Jesus' name we pray.

01:02:25.625 --> 01:02:26.066
Amen.

